A standalone application runs locally on your device and does not require the internet or a browser to function.

Installed directly on your system
Works offline (in most cases)

Examples:

Microsoft Word
VLC Media Player

A web application runs on a server and is accessed through a web browser over the internet.

No installation needed
Requires internet (usually)

Examples:

Gmail
Google Docs

Interview:
A standalone application runs locally on a device without needing the internet, while a web application runs on a server and is accessed through a browser over the internet.

Feature	                    Standalone Application	          Web Application
Runs on	                    Local machine	                    Server (accessed via browser)
Internet required	          No (mostly)	                      Yes
Installation	              Required	                        Not required
Updates	                    Manual	                          Automatic
Accessibility	              Single device	                    Any device with browser

